data.title: Archduchess Auguste Ferdinande of Austria
data.text:
Archduchess Auguste Ferdinande of Austria, Princess of Tuscany (Auguste Ferdinande Luise Maria Johanna Josepha; 1 April 1825 – 26 April 1864), was a daughter of Leopold II, Grand Duke o Tuscany, an his first wife, Maria Anna o Saxony. She married Prince Luitpold of Bavaria and was styled as Princess Luitpold.

Marriage[edit]

On 1 April 1844, Archduchess Auguste Ferdinande married Prince Luitpold of Bavaria, a son of King Ludwig I of Bavaria.

Issue[edit]

Ludwig III of Bavaria (7 January 1845 – 18 October 1921) married Archduchess Maria Theresa of Austria-Este and had issue.

Prince Leopold of Bavaria (9 February 1846 – 28 September 1930) married Archduchess Gisela of Austria and had issue.

Princess Therese of Bavaria (12 November 1850 – 19 December 1925) never married.

Prince Arnulf of Bavaria (6 July 1852 – 12 November 1907) married Princess Therese of Liechtenstein and had issue.

Titles and styles[edit]

1 April 1825 - 1 April 1844 Her Royal Highness Archduchess Auguste Ferdinande of Austria, Princess of Tuscany.

1 April 1844 - 26 April 1864 Her Royal Highness Princess Luitpold of Bavaria.
